<br>
Lo and behold, I found <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2913&amp;source=Live">Balance of Zebuxoruk</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, which, granted has nothing whatsoever to do with Protection from Evil, but it sure means that Paladins will be ESSENTIAL to raid groups when POP is released, if this spell goes live.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I thought perhaps a way to redesign the Protection from Evil spells would be to set them up like this:<br>
<br>
Minor Protection from Evil (level 30?  increase counter removal for higher level versions)<br>
<br>
slot 1:  Decrease Disease counter by 2 per tick<br>
slot 2:  Decrease Poison counter by 2 per tick<br>
<br>
Done this way, it wouldn't have any effect on the player except to reduce/remove the effects of Disease and Poison based spells.  The only question is if the &quot;Remove over time&quot; effect would be destroyed by an &quot;add xx Poison/disease counters&quot; effect.  Even if so, it would just mean recasting protection, which would remove the detrimental effect over time.  In that case, however, it would need to be called something different, since it wouldn't be protecting against evil, but rather mitigating the effects of evil.  Maybe &quot;Healing Spirit&quot; or something.<br>
<br>
Thoughts? <p><img src="http://www.emeraldis.com/~booraembj/smallbah.jpg" align=left> <br> <br> <br> <br> <BR> <center><font size=”3”><span style='filter:glow(color=#3CB371,strength=2);width:100%'> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268670" target="new">Aragir Lancot</a> </span><BR>
