</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirlageholyblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Lage Holyblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 7:49:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> I do have a rather stupid qestion.  Looking at Balance of Zebuxoruk, I don't see how its inclusion in PoP will make Paladins needed on raids.  Would you mind explaining that theory? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 990<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 7:55:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> Balance of Zebuxoruk reduces healing to 25%.  Presumably, since the intro of Focus items, that means that a cleric hit by Balance of Zebuxoruk would have his complete heal reduced to a 2500hp heal, instead of the current 10000.<br>
<br>
It also adds 9 curse counters.  As far as I am aware, paladins are the only class that can remove curses, is this not true?  That would mean every raid would need a paladin to Greater Remove Curse on their clerics anytime they get hit with BoZ.<br>
<br>
-Aragir (gotta fix that sig, it doesn't look at all like I hoped it would) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaallyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taallyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 8:07:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> Clerics, Druids, Shamans, and Paladins can use Remove Greater Curse. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69612">Baron Taallyn Nifesblade</a><BR>
Seventh Cavalry<BR>
Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirlageholyblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Lage Holyblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 8:18:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> Yes, 4 classes can.  I was thinking down that path also, but figured they could get any of those classes to do the curse removals.  Although, I didn't know shaman got it as well.  I thought it was druid/cleric/paladin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggorsmortus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RiggorsMortus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 595<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 8:23:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> But how many people have RGC?<br>
<br>
Drops off a few high-end luclin bosses i think <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umemnenthmoondust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Memnenth Moondust</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 1418<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 8:32:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://fallenalliance.org/screenshots/cecil_20020408123732.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> Balance is already prevalent in clearing for Glyphed/Exiled/Cursed - Xerkish - and Emperor battles.<br>
<br>
It's a pain, but not overly difficult to deal with.<br>
<br>
On a side not, Heal over times are NOT affected. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44702>Sir Memnenth </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umemnenthmoondust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Memnenth Moondust</A> at: 7/29/02 8:33:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 549<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 8:35:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> I think non-cleric classes (including Paladins) could be seen as a good choice for RGC and RC duty, because on tough encounters the clerics all might be busy with CH rotations and such.<br>
<br>
However with a PBAE effect like this, unless there is no damage AE along with it (i.e., the MT is the only one taking damage), you'd need an army of RGC/RC casters to keep the raid force curse-free.<br>
<br>
That is, unless PoP brings along with it a group version of RGC/RC, possibly with greater availability...<br>
<br>
Back to the original post, first I'd point out that curses aren't affected by disease/poison counter cures, so the AE spell you mentioned wouldn't be cured by the protection of evil idea you proposed.<br>
<br>
The other problem with a cure-over-time spell is that it would take up a spell icon, and with high end raids those come at a premium.  Direct cures are probably preferable because of this, although I suppose on certain encounters if curing the AE is the tough part then you might give something up to have the cure-over-time in place so that you don't need to keep spamming cures as much. <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Duke Aalek</a>
<BR>
60 Crusader
<BR>
Reign in Power
<BR>
Torvonnilous</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A> at: 7/29/02 8:41:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 993<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 9:32:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> Hmmm.  Let me clarify that I think paladins are so close to overbalanced now, that it's great.  I'm not suggesting these spells because we need them, I'm just suggesting them because when I thought of them a year ago, I thought they were a cool idea.  <br>
<br>
Paladins don't NEED Protection from Evil in ANY form.  It's just an idea I had and I wanted to think more about how to make it useful.<br>
<br>
That addressed, I did try to point out in my original post that Balance of Zebuxoruk has nothing to do with my idea for Protection vs Evil.  I just saw it and thought &quot;gee, remove curse is going to be really handy!&quot;<br>
<br>
Now, on to addressing the Protection vs. Evil idea!<br>
<br>
I thought perhaps a quick setup would help:<br>
<br>
Minor Protection Vs Evil (level 22)<br>
Increase max hp by 50<br>
Remove 2 disease counters per tick<br>
remove 2 poison counters per tick<br>
<br>
Lesser Protection Vs. Evil (level 30)<br>
Increase hp by 1 per tick<br>
Remove 4 disease counters per tick<br>
remove 4 poison counters per tick<br>
<br>
Protection Vs Evil (level 39)<br>
increase max hp by 50<br>
increase hp by 1 per tick<br>
remove 4 disease counters per tick<br>
remove 4 poison counters per tick<br>
<br>
Greater protection vs Evil (level 50)<br>
Increase max hp by 100<br>
Increase hp by 1 per tick<br>
remove 6 disease counters per tick<br>
remove 6 poison counters per tick<br>
<br>
Superior Protection vs Evil (level 59)<br>
Increase max hp by 150<br>
Increase hp by 2 per tick<br>
Remove 8 disease counters per tick<br>
remove 8 poison counters per tick<br>
Remove 2 curse counters per tick<br>
<br>
Group Protection Vs Evil (level 60)<br>
Increase max hp by 50<br>
Increase hp by 1 per tick<br>
Remove 4 disease counters per tick<br>
remove 4 poison counters per tick<br>
remove 1 curse counter per tick<br>
<br>
I dunno, maybe they should all be group spells?  Then that would make MassGroupBuff much more useful, and Superior Protection From Evil would seem pretty decent.<br>
<br>
But, as must be obvious, I know nothing of the high end encounters, and this might not be all that useful.  I just thought in places where you will run into a LOT of poison/disease based effects (thinking Plane of Decay here), a buff that removed those over time might be more valuable than having to have Abolish poison, Remove Greater Curse, and Counteract Disease memmed the whole time.<br>
<br>
-Aragir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaallyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taallyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 278<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 9:42:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Protection from Evil</span><hr size=1> It does appear that there will be more dots, curses, and disease/poison effects on mobs in PoP.  But a Cure over time will take a buff slot, and even now I sometimes have to drop a buff to let a Heal over Time in.  I think that a group direct cure spell would be more workable with limited buff slots available.  Something like a Curing Wave of Prexus (CWoP) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   that would remove disease, poison, and curse counters would be pretty interesting to counteract some of these PoP effects.  If it CWoP were made with a long recast time, then you'd still need several paladins to have effective coverage. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69612">Baron Taallyn Nifesblade</a><BR>
Seventh Cavalry<BR>
Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 995<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 9:59:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Curing Wave of Prexus</span><hr size=1> Hmmm.  Yeah, that sounds like a pretty good idea, although my original idea (back last year) had been to design a spell that would PREVENT Disease- or Poison-based negative effects from landing.  But that doesn't seem possible based on the change they made to the spell stacking code after UberGuild_01 exploited the Resurrection effect when fighting the 4th warder.<br>
<br>
Your idea sounds more like an &quot;Abolish Evil&quot; spell than a &quot;Curing Wave&quot; though.  To me, anyway.  Do you really think there would be much use for such a spell?<br>
<br>
-Aragir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaallyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taallyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 10:55:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curing Wave of Prexus</span><hr size=1> It depends on how many new effects there will be in PoP.  If there's only one in the very last zone, then it won't be that useful.  If everything in the Plane of Decay including Bertox's red-haired step newphew 4-times removed has an AE Curse/Disease/Poison proc and you have to go through that plane to advance further into the story, then a spell like CWoP could be very handy. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69612">Baron Taallyn Nifesblade</a><BR>
Seventh Cavalry<BR>
Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukoldanar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Koldanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 12:33:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curing Wave of Prexus</span><hr size=1> Let me just clarify something. This spell is cast as a targetable spell, and it affects heal spells that land on that target (if my guild explained it right).  Meaning, if the cleric had it on him, he'd still heal for full, but a CH would land on him for 25%...i had this effect on me during the Creator fight (yay rampage!) and CHs were only 2500 on me....clerics never had this cast on them. <p>Koldanar Bladesmith<BR>
Crusader of Novus Invictus
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21720"> Mah Stuff </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 993<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 7:24:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16134.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> forget tha buff icon</span><hr size=1> Just give paladins more group spells that will emulate their traditional holy auras.<br>
<br>
Cleansing Radiance<br>
remove 8 poison counters<br>
remove 8 disease counters<br>
targets: group<br>
radius: 100<br>
<br>
Divine Radiance<br>
remove 8 curse counters<br>
targets: group<br>
radius: 100<br>
<br>
Although more spells that can take advantage of tha AE group buff skill would be nice, really a paladin wants ter be able ter aid his group much like a bard without changing targets. Wave of Healing and Healing Wave of Prexus be something more worth adding to oor roles.<br>
